%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22Elon%20Musk%20spent%20Christmas%20Eve%20moving%20servers%20at%20one%20of%20X's%20data%20centers%20in%20Sacramento%2C%20in%20an%20example%20of%20his%20'recklessness'%20and%20'impatience%2C'%20biographer%20says%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Elon%20Musk%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6466294f7224930019f3602c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22576%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EElon%20Musk's%20new%20biography%20by%20Walter%20Isaacson%20was%20released%20on%20September%2012.%20%3Cp%3EClive%20Mason%20-%20Formula%201%2FFormula%201%20via%20Getty%20Image%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EElon%20Musk%20spent%20Christmas%20Eve%20moving%20X's%20data%20servers%20from%20one%20facility%20to%20another.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20facility%20was%20a%20major%20cost%20for%20X%2C%20according%20to%20Musk's%20new%20biography%20penned%20by%20Walter%20Isaacson.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIsaacson%20described%20Musk's%20behavior%20in%20this%20incident%20as%20an%C2%A0%26quot%3Bexample%20of%20his%20recklessness.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EElon%20Musk%20is%20infamous%20for%20his%20neurotic%20work%20ethic%20and%20no-nonsense%20approach%20to%20getting%20things%20done%20and%20Christmas%20Eve%20is%20no%20exception%20to%20this%2C%20according%20to%20an%20excerpt%20from%20his%20new%20biography%20written%20by%20Walter%20Isaacson%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2023%2F09%2F11%2Felon-musk-moved-twitter-servers-himself-in-the-night-new-biography-details-his-maniacal-sense-of-urgency.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ereported%20by%20CNBC%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShortly%20after%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-twitter-reach-agreement-to-close-acquisition-deal-2022-10%3Fr%3DUS%26IR%3DT%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EMusk's%20%2444%20billion%20takeover%20of%20X%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20then%20known%20as%20Twitter%20%E2%80%94%20in%20October%202022%2C%20he%20was%20keen%20to%20move%20servers%20from%20one%20of%20X's%20data%20centers%20in%20Sacramento%20to%20another%20facility%20in%20Portland%2C%20Oregon%20because%20it%20was%20costing%20the%20company%20over%20%24100%20million%2C%20per%20the%20excerpt.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20December%2022%2C%20Musk%20was%20in%20a%20meeting%20with%20two%20infrastructure%20managers%20who%20told%20him%20that%20NTT%20%E2%80%94%20the%20company%20that%20owned%20the%20Sacramento%20facility%20%E2%80%94%20had%20walked%20back%20on%20plans%20to%20move%20out%20the%20servers%20in%202023%20because%20%26quot%3Bthey%20don't%20think%20we%20will%20be%20financially%20viable.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20manager%20added%20that%20the%20operation%20would%20take%20at%20least%20six%20to%20nine%20months%20but%20Musk%20insisted%20it%20be%20done%20in%2090%20days%20or%20%26quot%3Byour%20resignation%20is%20accepted.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20manager%20protested%20Musk%20asked%3A%20%26quot%3BDo%20you%20know%20the%20head-explosion%20emoji%3F%26quot%3B%20He%20then%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BThat's%20what%20my%20head%20feels%20like%20right%20now.%20What%20a%20pile%20of%20fucking%20bullshit.%20Jesus%20H%20fucking%20Christ.%20Portland%20obviously%20has%20tons%20of%20room.%20It's%20trivial%20to%20move%20servers%20one%20place%20to%20another.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20Musk's%20cousins%20James%20and%20Andrew%20Musk%20who%20convinced%20him%20to%20move%20the%20servers%20themselves%20whilst%20they%20were%20on%20a%20plane%20from%20San%20Francisco%20to%20Austin%20the%20next%20day.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20the%20type%20of%20impulsive%2C%20impractical%2C%20surge-into-the-breach%20idea%20that%20Musk%20loved%2C%26quot%3B%20Isaacson%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20already%20late%20evening%2C%20but%20he%20told%20his%20pilot%20to%20divert%2C%20and%20they%20made%20a%20loop%20back%20up%20to%20Sacramento.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20group%20was%20let%20into%20the%20facility%20late%20at%20night%20by%20an%20X%20staffer%20named%20Alex%20from%20Uzbekistan%20who%20showed%20them%20the%20vault%20storing%20around%205%2C200%20computers%20on%20racks%20the%20size%20of%20refrigerators%2C%20weighing%20about%202%2C500%20pounds%20and%20eight%20feet%20tall.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20things%20do%20not%20look%20that%20hard%20to%20move%2C%26quot%3B%20Musk%20said%20but%20Alex%20pointed%20out%20that%20contractors%20needed%20to%20be%20hired%20to%20lift%20the%20floor%20panels%20and%20disconnect%20the%20electric%20cables%20and%20seismic%20rods%20underneath.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk%20then%20asked%20his%20security%20guard%20for%20a%20pocket%20knife%20and%20started%20lifting%20one%20of%20the%20air%20vents%20in%20the%20floor%20with%20it%20and%20opened%20the%20floor%20panels.%20He%20crawled%20under%20the%20server%20to%20open%20an%20electrical%20panel%20and%20when%20nothing%20exploded%2C%20he%20took%20it%20as%20a%20sign%20they%20could%20move%20ahead%20with%20the%20operation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20day%2C%20Christmas%20Eve%2C%20Musk%20called%20in%20reinforcements%20including%20friends%20from%20Tesla%2C%20SpaceX%2C%20and%20The%20Boring%20Company%20to%20procure%20equipment%20and%20tools%20needed%20to%20move%20the%20servers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoring%20Company%20CEO%20Steve%20Davis%20was%20able%20to%20get%20someone%20to%20obtain%20a%20semi-truck%20and%20line%20up%20moving%20vans%2C%20which%20the%20servers%20were%20wheeled%20onto.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20team%20used%20all%20of%20the%20available%20trucks%20in%20Sacramento%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%20week%20and%20moved%20over%20700%20racks%20in%20three%20days%2C%20with%20the%20rest%20being%20handled%20by%20X's%20infrastructure%20team%20in%20January.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk%20later%20admitted%20the%20%26quot%3Bwhole%20Sacramento%20shutdown%20was%20a%20mistake%2C%26quot%3B%20after%20the%20lack%20of%20servers%20caused%20a%20whole%20host%20of%20issues.%20This%20included%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-furious-after-ron-desantis-event-saw-app-crash-2023-5%3Fr%3DUS%26IR%3DT%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ERon%20Desantis'%20presidential%20campaign%20launch%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Twitter%20Spaces%20being%20spoiled%20by%20delays%20and%20glitches%20as%20the%20app%20repeatedly%20crashed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIsaacson%20wrote%20that%20Musk's%20Sacramento%20incident%20was%20%26quot%3Ban%20example%20of%20his%20recklessness%2C%20his%20impatience%20with%20pushback%2C%20and%20the%20way%20he%20intimidated%20people.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20the%20billionaire%20has%20%26quot%3Ba%20good%20track%20record%20of%20knowing%20when%20to%20ignore%20naysayers.%20But%20not%20a%20perfect%20one.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-christmas-eve-moving-x-servers-cut-costs-biography-2023-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694522538000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64edbd168f9177001939baa0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-christmas-eve-moving-x-servers-cut-costs-biography-2023-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22When%20two%20X%20managers%20told%20Elon%20Musk%20it%20would%20take%20nine%20months%20to%20move%20data%20servers%20from%20one%20facility%20to%20another%2C%20Musk%20insisted%20it%20happen%20in%2090%20days.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22sbhaimiya%40insider.com%20(Sawdah%20Bhaimiya)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-christmas-eve-moving-x-servers-cut-costs-biography-2023-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Retail%20Inflation%20Eases%20To%206.83%25%20In%20August%20From%207.44%25%20In%20July%22%2C%22con