ole.net%2Fen%2Fclimate%2Fcop27_fail_success_of_loss_and_damage%2F%5C%22%3Eloss%20and%20damage%20fund%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0for%20climate-vulnerable%20states%2C%20a%20new%20global%20norm%20has%20emerged%20around%20the%20idea%20of%20wealthier%20countries%20banding%20together%20to%20deliver%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oxfam.org%2Fen%2Fpress-releases%2Fg7-owes-huge-13-trillion-debt-global-south%23%3A~%3Atext%3DIn%2520April%252C%2520the%2520G7%2520agreed%2Cclimate%2520finance%2520goal%2520by%25202025.%5C%22%3Eclimate-related%20assistance%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0to%20the%20Global%20South.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENot%20surprisingly%2C%20climate%20change%20is%20a%20prime%20focus%20of%20the%20summit%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmea.gov.in%2FImages%2FCPV%2FG20-New-Delhi-Leaders-Declaration.pdf%5C%22%3Ejoint%20statement%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0published%20on%20Saturday.%20The%20%E2%80%9CGreen%20Development%20Pact%20for%20a%20Sustainable%20Future%E2%80%9D%20section%20runs%20to%20eight%20pages%20%E2%80%93%20longer%20than%20any%20other%20topic%20%E2%80%93%20and%20covers%20subjects%20ranging%20from%20clean%20energy%20transitions%20and%20emissions%20cuts%20to%20climate%20finance%20and%20plastic%20pollution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20yet%2C%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmea.gov.in%2FImages%2FCPV%2FG20-New-Delhi-Leaders-Declaration.pdf%5C%22%3EDelhi%20Declaration%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0still%20falls%20short%20on%20climate.%20It%20features%20extensive%20pledges%20to%20fight%20climate%20change%2C%20but%20most%20don%E2%80%99t%20offer%20specific%20targets%20or%20timeframes.%20Additionally%2C%20the%20document%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20set%20specific%20mitigation%20goals%20and%20targets%20for%20G20%20countries%20themselves.%20Rather%2C%20the%20focus%20is%20more%20on%20contributing%20to%20global%20mitigation%20efforts%3A%20%E2%80%9CWe%20reiterate%20our%20commitment%20to%20achieve%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eglobal%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0net%20zero%20GHG%20emissions%2Fcarbon%20neutrality%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9CWill%20pursue%20and%20encourage%20efforts%20to%20triple%20renewable%20energy%20capacity%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eglobally%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0through%20existing%20targets%20and%20policies%E2%80%9D%20(emphases%20mine).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20little%20doubt%20that%20the%20varying%20national%20situations%20of%20member%20states%20make%20it%20hard%20to%20set%20common%20goals%20and%20targets%20for%20pursuit%20at%20home.%20But%20that%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20have%20to%20prevent%20the%20G20%20from%2C%20say%2C%20deciding%20on%20separate%20common%20emissions%20reduction%20targets%20for%20developed%20and%20developing%20members.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20inconvenient%20truth%20is%20that%2C%20despite%20genuine%20commitments%20to%20promote%20a%20greener%20planet%2C%20so%20many%20G20%20members%20are%20still%20locked%20into%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Findia-climate-change-g20-cop28-c25dd753a2f8f520261ec4858b921a1a%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAccording%2520to%2520a%2520report%2520by%2Ct%2520have%2520carbon%2520capture%2520technologies.%5C%22%3Eold%20and%20dirty%20energy%20habits%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20lessens%20the%20likelihood%20of%20upholding%20pledges%20on%20curbing%20emissions%2C%20and%20helps%20explain%20why%20many%20of%20the%20Delhi%20Declaration%E2%80%99s%20climate%20commitments%20are%20vague.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20G20%20members%20spent%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.carbonbrief.org%2Fdaily-brief%2Fg20-countries-gave-record-1-4tn-to-support-fossil-fuels-in-2022-report%2F%5C%22%3Erecord%20amount%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0on%20fossil%20fuels.%20According%20to%20energy%20think%20tank%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fember-climate.org%2Finsights%2Fresearch%2Fg20-per-capita-coal-power-emissions-2023%2F%5C%22%3EEmber%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20multiple%20G20%20countries%20saw%20major%20rises%20in%20per%20capita%20emissions%20over%20the%20past%20seven%20years%2C%20including%20Indonesia%20(56%25)%2C%20Turkiye%20(41%25)%2C%20China%20(30%25)%2C%20and%20India%20(29%25).%20Many%20G20%20members%2C%20most%20notably%20China%20and%20India%2C%20remain%20heavily%20reliant%20on%20coal%2C%20though%20Australia%20and%20South%20Korea%20were%20the%20top%20two%20G20%20coal%20power%20polluters%20in%202022%2C%20according%20to%20Ember.%20They%20emitted%20more%20than%20triple%20the%20global%20average.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20sure%2C%20many%20G20%20countries%20have%20not%20only%20pledged%20to%20reduce%20emissions%20but%20also%20taken%20concrete%20steps%20toward%20that%20goal.%20However%2C%20a%20continued%20dependence%20on%20dirty%20fuels%20has%20undermined%20that%20goal%2C%20and%20weakened%20incentives%20within%20the%20G20%20to%20take%20more%20robust%20steps%20to%20tackle%20climate%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F11%2F11122254%2Fli-an-lim-ycW4YxhrWHM-unsplash-1.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F11%2F11122254%2Fli-an-lim-ycW4YxhrWHM-unsplash-1.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F11%2F11122254%2Fli-an-lim-ycW4YxhrWHM-unsplash-1-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F11%2F11122254%2Fli-an-lim-ycW4YxhrWHM-unsplash-1-1024x683.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-563686%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPlacard%20at%20a%20climate%20change%20protest%20in%20San%20Francisco.%20Photo%3A%20Unplash%2FLi-An%20Lim.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%2C%20the%20current%20G20%20president%20and%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.statista.com%2Fstatistics%2F263455%2Fprimary-energy-consumption-of-selected-countries%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DChina%2520is%2520the%2520largest%2520consumer%2Csuch%2520as%2520oil%2520and%2520coal.%5C%22%3E%C2%A0third-largest%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0energy%20consumer%2C%20offers%20a%20sobering%20case%20study.%20At%20the%202021%20UN%20climate%20summit%20in%20Glasgow%2C%20Modi%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-india-59125143%5C%22%3Epledged%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0to%20make%20India%20a%20net%20zero%20nation%20by%202070.%20Since%20then%2C%20his%20government%20and%20India%E2%80%99s%20private%20sector%20have%20implemented%20a%20flurry%20of%20policies%20to%20kickstart%20India%E2%80%99s%20carbon%20transition.%20In%20the%20last%20six%20months%20alone%2C%20major%20Indian%20conglomerates%20have%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2023-03-03%2Fadani-ambani-plan-to-build-25gw-of-clean-energy-in-indian-state%5C%22%3Epledged%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0new%20clean%20energy%20investments%2C%20and%20the%20power%20ministry%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pv-magazine.com%2F2023%2F04%2F06%2Findia-to-annually-tender-50-gw-of-renewables-over-next-5-years%2F%5C%22%3Eannounced%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0it%20will%20accept%20bids%20for%2050%20gigawatts%20of%20clean%20energy%20capacity%20for%20the%20next%20five%20years.%20New%20Delhi%20has%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.economictimes.com%2Fmarkets%2Fstocks%2Fnews%2Fbharat-petroleum-to-raise-2-19-billion-in-green-energy-push%2Farticleshow%2F101343177.cms%5C%22%3Ecommitted%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0billions%20in%20assistance%20to%20top%20state-owned%20hydrocarbon%20firms%20to%20support%20their%20clean%20energy%20transitions.%20The%20government%20has%20also%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.power-technology.com%2Fnews%2Findia-five-year-pause-coal-power%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520Indian%2520Government%2520will%2520not%2Cto%2520increase%2520its%2520renewable%2520capacity.%5C%22%3Epledged%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0not%20to%20build%20new%20coal%20power%20plants%20for%20five%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20New%20Delhi%20has%20signalled%20an%20intention%20to%20diversify%20its%20fledgling%20renewable%20energy%20mix.%20It%20has%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Fnews%2Findian-govts-multibillion-dollar-subsidy-to-boosts-battery-makers-in-clean-energy-drive-report-11687917051760.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520Indian%2520government%2520is%2520developing%2CIndia%2527s%2520shift%2520towards%2520clean%2520energy.%5C%22%3Eproposed%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0a%20USD%202.6%20billion%20subsidy%20package%20for%20the%20next%20seven%20years%20for%20companies%20that%20produce%20electricity%20batteries%2C%20to%20ramp%20up%20solar%20energy%20storage%20capacity%2C%20but%20it%20is%20also%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hydrogeninsight.com%2Fproduction%2Findian-green-hydrogen-subsidies-set-to-be-about-90-lower-than-us-tax-credits-reports%2F2-1-1431539%5C%22%3Eoffering%20subsidies%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20encourage%20the%20production%20of%20green%20hydrogen.%20The%20government%20has%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.voanews.com%2Fa%2Findia-makes-2-3-billion-green-hydrogen-push-to-meet-climate-goals%2F6906977.html%5C%22%3Ecommitted%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0USD%202%20billion%20to%20develop%20its%20green%20hydrogen%20sector%2C%20and%20it%20is%20also%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.financialexpress.com%2Fopinion%2Fgreen-ammonia-is-the-next-step-in-indias-quest-for-energy-and-food-security%2F3023838%2F%5C%22%3Efocused%20on%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0green%20ammonia%2C%20a%20derivate%20of%20green%20hydrogen.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-cd-pull-quote%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20dirty%20habits%20die%20hard.%20Coal%20constitutes%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.spglobal.com%2Fcommodityinsights%2Fen%2Fmarket-insights%2Flatest-news%2Fcoal%2F060322-india-expected-to-commission-10-thermal-coal-power-plants-in-2022-23-add-7010-mw%5C%22%3E75%25%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%20India%E2%80%99s%20electricity%20and%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.spglobal.com%2Fcommodityinsights%2Fen%2Fmarket-insights%2Flatest-news%2Fcoal%2F080122-india-prefers-coal-for-its-abundance-availability-affordability-state-owned-producer%5C%22%3E70%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.spglobal.com%2Fcommodityinsights%2Fen%2Fmarket-insights%2Flatest-news%2Fcoal%2F080122-india-prefers-coal-for-its-abundance-availability-affordability-state-owned-producer%5C%22%3E%25%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%20total%20energy%20production.%20Coal%20production%20has%20increased%20by%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleaseIframePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D1925521%23%3A~%3Atext%3DDuring%2520the%2520last%2520nine%2520years%2Cthe%2520history%2520of%2520the%2520country.%5C%22%3Enearly%2050%25%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0over%20the%20last%20nine%20years.%20This%20past%20year%2C%20state-owned%20Coal%20India%2C%20which%20accounts%20for%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fmarkets%2Fcommodities%2Fcoal-india-surpasses-annual-output-target-first-time-17-years-2023-03-31%2F%5C%22%3E80%25%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%20India%E2%80%99s%20coal%20output%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fmarkets%2Fcommodities%2Fcoal-india-surpasses-annual-output-target-first-time-17-years-2023-03-31%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DCoal%2520India%2520surpasses%2520annual%2520output%2520target%2520for%2520first%2520time%2520in%252017%2520years%2C-By%2520Sudarshan%2520Varadhan%26amp%3Btext%3DSINGAPORE%252C%2520March%252031%2520(Reuters)%2Cthat%2520ended%2520in%2520March%25202006.%5C%22%3Esurpassed%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0its%20annual%20production%20targets%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%2017%20years.%20And%20it%E2%80%99s%20full%20speed%20ahead.%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.economictimes.com%2Findustry%2Findl-goods%2Fsvs%2Fmetals-mining%2F22-companies-submit-bids-for-commercial-coal-mining-auction%2Farticleshow%2F101341946.cms%23%3A~%3Atext%3DSynopsis%2Cfollowed%2520by%2520other%2520selected%2520mines.%5C%22%3EIn%20January%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%2022%20companies%20submitted%2035%20bids%20to%20extract%20coal%20from%2018%20different%20coal%20mines%20across%20the%20country.%20In%20March%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20coal%20minister%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mining-technology.com%2Fnews%2Findia-to-start-exporting-coal%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DPralhad%2520Joshi%252C%2520India%2527s%2520minister%2520for%2C2026%252C%2520Times%2520of%2520India%2520reports.%5C%22%3Epredicted%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0that%20by%202026%2C%20India%20will%20be%20so%20flush%20with%20coal%20it%20will%20be%20able%20to%20start%20exporting%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20isn%E2%80%99t%20just%20a%20story%20about%20coal.%20Domestic%20petroleum%20production%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Feconomy%2Fdomestic-crude-oil-production-up-2-1-to-2-5-mmt-in-july-imports-decline-6-3-yoy-ppac-11692702658786.html%5C%22%3Eincreased%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0nearly%204%25%2C%20and%20natural%20gas%20more%20than%208%25%2C%20between%20July%202022%20and%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20for%20all%20the%20talk%20of%20Indian%20companies%20transitioning%20to%20renewables%2C%20that%20won%E2%80%99t%20be%20easy.%20India%E2%80%99s%20Reserve%20Bank%20recently%20warned%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20powerful%20industrial%20and%20agricultural%20sectors%2C%20which%20contribute%20major%20shares%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20total%20emissions%2C%20could%20be%20obstacles%20to%20a%20greener%20economy.%20Additionally%2C%20with%20India%E2%80%99s%20carbon%20tax%20rate%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fearth.org%2Findia-carbon-tax%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DIndia%2527s%2520carbon%2520tax%2520rate%2520is%2Cexample%2520for%2520other%2520G20%2520countries.%5C%22%3Eamong%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20lowest%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20many%20firms%20could%20simply%20swallow%20the%20costs%20and%20not%20ramp%20up%20renewables.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EG20%20joint%20statements%20aren%E2%80%99t%20binding.%20There%E2%80%99s%20nothing%20lost%20by%20setting%20out%20pledges%20with%20specific%20targets%20and%20timeframes%2C%20instead%20of%20general%20commitments.%20That%20this%20didn%E2%80%99t%20happen%20likely%20reflects%20many%20G20%20members%E2%80%99%20inability%20to%20uphold%20such%20pledges%2C%20and%20their%20continued%20attachment%20to%20the%20very%20polluting%20policies%20that%20contributed%20to%20climate%20change%20in%20the%20first%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EMichael%20Kugelman%20is%20the%20director%20of%20the%20South%20Asia%20Institute%20at%20the%20Wilson%20Center%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thethirdpole.net%2Fen%2Fclimate%2Fopinion-g20s-delhi-declaration-falls-predictably-short-on-climate%2F%5C%22%3Earticle%3C%2Fa%3E%20first%20appeared%20on%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thethirdpole.net%2Fen%2F%5C%22%3EThe%20Third%20Pole%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694518255000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F11114758%2FF5pyYTUbgAAvUgc.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fg20-why-many-of-the-delhi-declarations-climate-commitments-are-vague%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Although%20climate%20change%20is%20the%20prime%20focus%20of%20the%20summit's%20joint%20statement%2C%20the%C2%A0Delhi%20Declaration%C2%A0falls%20short%20on%20climate%20without%20specific%20targets%20and%20timeframes.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fg20-why-many-of-the-delhi-declarations-climate-commitments-are-vague%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Red%20Fire%20Ants%20With%20Painful%20Bites%20Posing%20Threat%20To%20Europe%2C%20Researchers%20Warn%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ERed%20fire%20ants%2C%20a%20known%20invasive%20species%20in%20the%20United%20States%20and%20Australia%2C%20have%20recently%20been%20detected%20in%20Sicily%2C%20Italy.%20Researchers%20have%20raised%20concerns%20about%20the%20possibility%20of%20their%20spread%20to%20other%20parts%20of%20Europe%2C%20which%20could%20have%20significant%20consequences%20for%20the%20environment%2C%20public%20health%2C%20and%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20red%20fire%20ant%2C%20scientifically%20known%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Ftopics%2Fimmunology-and-microbiology%2Fsolenopsis-invicta%5C%22%3ESolenopsis%20invicta%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20is%20notorious%20for%20its%20dangerous%20sting%2C%20which%20can%20be%20painful%20and%20occasionally%20pose%20health%20risks%2C%20especially%20to%20individuals%20who%20are%20allergic%20to%20its%20venom.%20Additionally%2C%20these%20ants%20are%20known%20to%20cause%20damage%20to%20crops%2C%20leading%20to%20agricultural%20losses%2C%20and%20they%20have%20the%20unusual%20ability%20to%20infest%20electrical%20equipment%2C%20including%20cars%20and%20computers.%20This%20unique%20behaviour%20can%20result%20in%20technical%20malfunctions%20and%20costly%20repairs%2C%20making%20the%20presence%20of%20red%20fire%20ants%20a%20multifaceted%20problem%20wherever%20they%20establish%20themselves%20as%20invasive%20species.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20article%20published%20in%20the%20journal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fpii%2FS0960982223009740%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ECurrent%20Biology%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3Eon%20September%2011%2C%20a%20group%20of%20ant%20experts%20confirmed%20that%20the%20species%20has%20made%20its%20way%20to%20Sicily-the%20ant's%20first%20official%20sighting%20in%20Europe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BS.%20invicta%20is%20one%20of%20the%20worst%20invasive%20species.%20It%20can%20spread%20alarmingly%20quickly%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20lead%20author%20Mattia%20Menchetti%20of%20the%20Institute%20of%20Evolutionary%20Biology%20in%20Spain.%20%26quot%3BFinding%20this%20species%20in%20Italy%20was%20a%20big%20surprise%2C%20but%20we%20knew%20this%20day%20would%20come.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20it%20originated%20in%20South%20America%2C%20S.%20invicta%20has%20spread%20quickly%2C%20flying%20into%20wind%20streams%20to%20travel%20farther%20on%20the%20local%20level.%20But%20humans%20have%20also%20helped%20it%20spread%20both%20through%20the%20maritime%20trade%20industry%20and%20by%20shipping%20plant%20products%2C%20enabling%20it%20to%20establish%20itself%20in%20Australia%2C%20China%2C%20the%20Caribbean%2C%20Mexico%2C%20and%20throughout%20the%20United%20States%20in%20less%20than%20a%20century.%20Europe%20has%20evaded%20them%20for%20longer%20than%20expected%2C%20say%20the%20researchers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20a%20vast%20number%20of%20alien%20ant%20species%20currently%20establishing%20themselves%20in%20Europe%2C%20and%20the%20absence%20of%20this%20species%20was%20kind%20of%20a%20relief%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Menchetti.%20%26quot%3BFor%20decades%2C%20scientists%20have%20feared%20that%20it%20would%20arrive.%20We%20could%20not%20believe%20our%20eyes%20when%20we%20saw%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694518200000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-09%2Frs5enhn_the-red-imported-fire-ant-solenopsis-invicta-is-a-venomous-species_625x300_12_September_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fred-fire-ants-with-painful-bites-posing-threat-to-europe-researchers-warn-4382926%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Researchers%20have%20reported%20the%20discovery%20of%2088%20red%20fire%20ant%20nests%20covering%20an%20area%20of%20approximately%205%20hectares%20near%20the%20city%20of%20Syracuse%20in%20Sicily%2C%20Italy.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fred-fire-ants-with-painful-bites-posing-threat-to-europe-researchers-warn-4382926%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fred-fire-ants-with-painful-bites-posing-threat-to-europe-researchers-warn-4