20revealed.%20The%20study%2C%20published%20in%20the%20British%20Journal%20of%20Surgery%20(BJS)%20and%20shared%20with%20the%20%3Cem%3EBBC%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20examined%20sexual%20conduct%20in%20the%20UK%20surgical%20workforce%20over%20the%20past%20five%20years.%20It%20found%20that%20almost%20one%20in%20three%20female%20surgeons%20working%20in%20the%20NHS%20(National%20Health%20Service)%20have%20been%20sexually%20assaulted%20by%20colleagues.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Facademic.oup.com%2Fbjs%2Fadvance-article%2Fdoi%2F10.1093%2Fbjs%2Fznad242%2F7264733%3Fsearchresult%3D1%26login%3Dfalse%5C%22%3Esurvey%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20registered%20surgeons%20-%20men%20and%20women%20-%20were%20invited%20to%20take%20part%20completely%20anonymously%20and%201%2C434%20responded.%20It%20found%20that%2030%25%20of%20female%20surgeons%20who%20responded%20said%20they%20had%20been%20sexually%20assaulted%2C%2029%25%20of%20women%20had%20experienced%20unwanted%20physical%20advances%20at%20work%2C%20over%2040%25%20had%20received%20uninvited%20comments%20about%20their%20body%20and%2038%25%20received%20sexual%20%26quot%3Bbanter%26quot%3B%20at%20work.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B90%25%20of%20women%2C%20and%2081%25%20of%20men%2C%20had%20witnessed%20some%20form%20of%20sexual%20misconduct%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fhealth-66775015%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EBBC%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported%20citing%20the%20study.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20survey%20concluded%20that%20men%20and%20women%20surgeons%20are%20%26quot%3Bliving%20different%20realities%26quot%3B.%20%26quot%3BSexual%20misconduct%20occurs%20frequently%20and%20appears%20to%20go%20unchecked%20in%20the%20surgical%20environment%20owing%20to%20a%20combination%20of%20a%20deeply%20hierarchical%20structure%20and%20a%20gender%20and%20power%20imbalance.%20The%20result%20is%20an%20unsafe%20working%20environment%20and%20an%20unsafe%20space%20for%20patients%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20added%2C%20as%20per%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Ftheguardian.com%2Fsociety%2F2023%2Fsep%2F12%2Ffemale-surgeons-nhs-sexually-assaulted-metoo%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Guardian%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAlso%20Read%20%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Ftaken-hostage-in-kuwait-in-1990-uk-passengers-crew-to-sue-british-airways-4381776%5C%22%3ETaken%20Hostage%20In%20Kuwait%20In%201990%2C%20UK%20Passengers%2C%20Crew%20To%20Sue%20British%20Airways%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20survey%20also%20found%20that%20there%20is%20a%20lack%20of%20faith%20in%20bodies%20such%20as%20NHS%20Trust%2C%20the%20General%20Medical%20Council%20and%20the%20Royal%20Colleges%20to%20tackle%20the%20problem.%20Only%2015.1%25%20of%20women%20regarded%20the%20GMC%20as%20adequate%20in%20their%20handling%20of%20sexual%20misconduct.%20Evaluations%20of%20National%20Health%20Service%20Trusts%20were%20comparatively%20low.%20Only%2015.8%25%20of%20women%20rated%20them%20as%20adequate%20and%2044.9%25%20of%20men.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20need%20a%20major%20change%20in%20investigation%20processes%20so%20they%20become%20external%20and%20independent%2C%20and%20are%20trusted%20in%20order%20for%20healthcare%20to%20become%20a%20safer%20place%20to%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Professor%20Carrie%20Newlands%2C%20consultant%20surgeon%20from%20the%20University%20of%20Surrey.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurther%2C%20the%20report%20said%20that%20for%20staff%2C%20workplace%20harassment%20could%20be%20detrimental%20to%20their%20physical%20and%20mental%20health%2C%20with%20cases%20even%20leading%20to%20self-harm%20and%20victims%20contemplating%20suicide.%20The%20researchers%20called%20for%20action%20to%20improve%20the%20culture%20in%20the%20surgical%20workforce%20and%20%26quot%3Bcreate%20adequate%20mechanisms%20to%20deal%20with%20perpetrators%26quot%3B.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694512740000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22http